children.subject: Data 8 and Data 100 are related, although you can get away with going straight into Data 100. There are lots of students who do it, and it should be fine as long as you feel comfortable with your programming skills. In terms of workload, Data 100 is lighter than most other upper division CS classes you take, so that schedule seems manageable depending on how much time you're willing to put in and how your experience has been in previous classes. 61B and 16B will probably take up more time than Data 100, so if you struggled with 61A or 16A it might be a little rough. Otherwise, it's probably fine.
